---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Jamie Shiers"
  description="Operations & Quality Manager in UK aerospace manufacturing. Founder of Parola Development."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-wrap">
      <header class="about-header">
        <p class="eyebrow mono">About</p>
        <h1>Jamie Shiers</h1>
        <p class="tagline">Operations & Quality Manager · Aerospace Manufacturing · Founder, <a href="https://parola.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Parola Development</a></p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I work as Operations & Quality Manager at a small UK aerospace manufacturer,
          where I wear most of the hats — quality systems, IT infrastructure, supply chain
          compliance, business development, and anything else that needs doing on a given day.
        </p>
        <p>
          My current focus is leading the company's certification journey through
          AS9100D / EN9100, Cyber Essentials, and JOSCAR supplier qualification — while
          keeping the day-to-day running smoothly. I write here to share what I'm learning,
          both for my own clarity and in the hope it's useful to others navigating the same terrain.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside the day job, I run <a href="https://parola.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Parola Development</a> —
          a small IT consultancy helping other UK SMEs with managed IT, Microsoft 365, and
          cyber security. Cyber Essentials implementation is a particular focus there.
        </p>

        <h2>What I write about</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>AS9100D & EN9100</strong> — practical implementation in small manufacturers, not the theory</li>
          <li><strong>Cyber Essentials</strong> — step-by-step guides for businesses without a dedicated IT team</li>
          <li><strong>Operations</strong> — quality management, supply chain, JOSCAR, AQAP, and the realities of small-team operations</li>
          <li><strong>Technology</strong> — Microsoft 365, infrastructure, and the tools that keep small businesses running</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Background</h2>
        <p>
          Based in the West Midlands, UK. Working in aerospace and defence supply chain.
          Interested in the intersection of operational discipline and practical technology.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          The best way to reach me is via <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jamieshiers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
          For Parola Development enquiries, use the contact form at <a href="https://parola.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">parola.dev</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-wrap {
    max-width: 620px;
    padding: 48px 0 80px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }
  .tagline {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .tagline a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .tagline a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
